Let the two integer roots be $\alpha, \beta$. Then, from $\alpha+\beta=-\frac{1}{a}$ being an integer, we know that the positive number $a=\frac{1}{n}$ (where $n$ is a positive integer).
Thus, the original equation can be written as
$$
x^{2}+n x+n^{2}-13=0 \text {. }
