By $\Delta=n^{2}-4\left(n^{2}-13\right)=52-3 n^{2} \geqslant 0$
$$
\Rightarrow n^{2} \leqslant \frac{52}{3} \text {. }
$$

Therefore, $n$ can take $1,2,3, 4$.
When $n=1$, the original equation is $x^{2}+x-12=0$, which has two integer roots;

When $n=2$, the original equation is $x^{2}+2 x-9=0$, which has no integer roots;

